∀x (Jumps(x) → Likes(jane, x)) ::: If an animal jumps, then Jane likes it.
∀x (Legs(x) → Jumps(x)) ::: If an animal has legs, then it jumps.

¬(Jumps(kiki) ∨ Legs(kiki)) → (Terricolous(kiki) ∨ Legs(kiki)) ::: If KiKi neither jumps nor has legs, then KiKi is terricolous or has legs.

Barks(kiki) ∧ Dog(kiki) ::: KiKi barks and is a dog.
